thread.title: Woman, 23, dies in crash involving baby on A92
thread.title_full: Woman, 23, dies in crash involving baby on A92

title: Woman, 23, dies in crash involving baby on A92
text:
Woman, 23, dies in crash involving baby on A92 18 February 2017 Close share panel Image copyright NEWSLINE MEDIA LTD A woman has died after a car with a baby on board crashed and overturned in Aberdeenshire. 
The incident happened on the A92 north of Inverbervie at 11:00 on Saturday. 
The 23-year-old driver died at the scene. The 13-month-old girl suffered minor injuries and was airlifted to Aberdeen Royal Infirmary. 
Police Scotland said no other vehicles were involved. The road was closed for several hours but has now re-opened.
